closureNotices.title: Pennsylvania State Forest: Road closures (see notice for details)
closureNotices.detailText:
Please note the following updates to road closures and openings in Pennsylvania and Roseberg State Forests:
Colo road is closed where it enters Pennsylvania from Trunkey Ck side  at this point it becomes Carrollina road. The reason for closure is due to haulage operations.
Carrollina road is closed to public access throughout Pennsylvania and Roseberg (so the entire east-west road) again due to haulage from operations within Pennsylvania and haulage from Roseberg which heads east to Colo road. This includes crossing Carrollina Rd to access areas to the south.
Rocky Bridge crossing is open; however the road is not open to the public.
Kentucky road from Neville is open, however Carrollina is not.
Tea Tree road into Roseberg is also closed. It will remain closed for the foreseeable future; however we hope to be able to push the road closure at the start of Pennsylvania (where it becomes Carrollina) further west in the near future.

structuredImpact.rationale: Multiple roads including Carrollina and Tea Tree are closed to public access due to haulage operations, indicating vehicle access is closed; camping impact is not mentioned.

closureNotices.title: Penrose State Forest closed - Limited camping only off Paddys River Road
closureNotices.detailText:
Penrose State Forests has been closed due to serious concerns for visitor safety.
Hazardous road conditions, created by vehicles using roads during wet weather, forced this closure.
Find out more about visiting sustainably.
Restoration work has commenced however it is extensive and weather-dependent. Visitors can access the designated camp areas via the advised routes.
Low impact recreational activities (non-vehicle) are permitted in the closed forest. Locally Wingello State Forest has partially reopened and is an option for vehicle recreational activities. Observe all signage and please visit sustainably.
A 400m area off Paddys River Road will remain open for camping.
Access only via Penrose Forest Way. Nearest facilities are located at Kingsbury VC rest area.
Visitors may park safety off Penrose Forest Way.

structuredImpact.rationale: Camping is limited to a 400m area off Paddys River Road and access is only via Penrose Forest Way; hazardous road conditions have caused closure and restricted vehicle access.

follow all signage, barricades and directions from Forestry Corporation staff

closureNotices.title: Masseys Creek State Forest campgrounds closed due to bushfire impact
closureNotices.detailText:
Bushfires are currently burning in the Upper Allyn area and are affecting some State forests. Campgrounds in the following State forests are closed while fire operations are underway:
Chichester State Forest (Allyn River)  north-west of Dungog. Includes Old Camp Campground, Ladies Well, Dobbie Rim Campground, Pademelon Campground, Allyn River Forest Rest Area/Campground, White Rock Campground, Peach Tree Picnic Area.
Masseys Creek State Forest  north-west of Dungog
Alternative campgrounds remain open at Chichester State Forest (Telegherry River)  North of Dungog.
You can stay up to date on bushfires by visiting the NSW Rural Fire Service website or using the NSW Hazards Near Me app.

structuredImpact.rationale: Campgrounds in Masseys Creek State Forest are explicitly closed due to bushfire impact; no information on vehicle access.

closureNotices.title: Putty State Forest: partly closed
closureNotices.detailText:
Please note that areas pf Putty State Forest remains closed over the longer term due to significant impact from severe weather and bushfires.
Putty State Forest consists of two areas. One is managed by Forestry Corporation, the other, a Flora Reserve, managed by the National Parks and Wildlife Service.
This advisory refers only to the area managed by Forestry Corporation - a defined area generally the eastern part of Putty State Forest.
Commission Road and a section of Main Hunter Trail are currently opened. All other roads, tracks and fire trails including their parts within the defined area remain closed.
For information on roads outside the definite area, within Flora Reserve, please contact the National Parks and Wildlife Service.

structuredImpact.rationale: Most roads and tracks in the Forestry Corporation area are closed, limiting vehicle access and camping.
